  <discussion type="conservation">of conservation concern;</discussion>
  <discussion>Variety scribneri is poorly known and seldom collected. It is distinguished by its relatively larger heads and narrower leaves and its indument (in a region where var. integerrimus is notably glabrate).</discussion>
